OL,6,FIn response, Jersey's Cabinet Office
OL,7,Fsays: "Whilst the cleaning can be seen
OL,8,Fas beneficial, there are unintended
OL,9,Fconsequences of abrasive and strong
OL,10,Fchemical cleaning that erode the
OL,11,Fnatural stone grave markers
OL,12,Funnecessarily.
OL,14,F"This causes a larger surface area to
OL,15,Fbe exposed to become dirtier sooner
OL,16,Fand leads to quicker regrowth of the
OL,17,Fbiological fauna, arguably requiring
OL,18,Fmore frequent cleaning. This leads to
OL,19,Fswifter erosion making the
OL,20,Finscriptions degrade each time.
